{
  "texts": [
    "As the example in Fig. 6, Topic#1 about Ukraine and Russia evolves from the year 2020 to 2022.",
    "Due to the emergence of the word \"invasion\", we see Topic#1 captures the Ukraine-Russia war that exploded in 2022.",
    "Similarly, Topic#K about Covid-19 evolves from the year 2020 to 2022 with the explosion of the Omicron variant.",
    "These topic evolution reveals how topics emerge, grow, and vanish, which has been applied for trend analysis and opinion mining.",
    "Dieng et al (2019) first propose a neural dynamic topic model, the Dynamic Embedding Topic Model."
  ]
}